uild With GFF tools, Resources, and Company pages. Include clickable example searches: Build AI for Banking, Create University AI Lab, Insurance AI, Mining AI, Retail AI, Build AI GCC. Results must appear instantly when typing or clicking examples. Each result must show title, category, short description, and route link. No API calls. No backend. No fake data. Design must be premium, clean, Apple-like, and consistent with the current landing theme. Use subtle Framer Motion or CSS transitions if available. Avoid box-inside-box clutter, excessive pills, badge soup, and neon overload. Mobile must be excellent. Acceptance: section appears after hero, search works locally, examples work, empty state is polished, links resolve, build passes.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 41 |   },\\\\n 42 |   {\\\\n 43 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"05-homepage-garage-foundry-factory-journey\\\\\\\",\\\\n 44 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Complete Garage Foundry Factory journey\\\\\\\",\\\\n 45 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 46 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Garage Foundry Factory journey\\\\\\\",\\\\n 47 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 48 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Verify or restore the homepage transformation journey. It must include Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. Use the existing approved landing section if one already maps to this. Do not create duplicates. Do not redesign approved sections unnecessarily. Each step should have a concise description, outcome, and route link: Garage /platforms/garage, Foundry /platforms/foundry, Factory /platforms/factory, Operate /capabilities/operations or /platforms/control-center, Optimize /platforms/control-center, Scale /platforms/factory. UI should feel premium, like an enterprise operating model timeline, with subtle motion and responsive vertical mobile layout. Avoid visual clutter. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 49 |   },\\\\n 50 |   {\\\\n 51 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"06-homepage-what-we-build\\\\\\\",\\\\n 52 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Complete What We Build section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 53 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 54 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What We Build capabilities section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 55 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 56 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Verify or restore the homepage What We Build section. It must include these required cards: AI Strategy, AI Engineering, Agentic AI, AI Governance, AI Labs, AI Factory, AI Marketplace, AI Operations. Use existing approved card/grid design if present. Do not duplicate an existing capabilities section. Add links: AI Strategy /capabilities/strategy, AI Engineering /capabilities/engineering, Agentic AI /capabilities/agents, AI Governance /capabilities/governance, AI Labs /capabilities/labs, AI Factory /platforms/factory or /capabilities/operations, AI Marketplace /platforms/marketplace, AI Operations /capabilities/operations. Include secondary references where natural: Knowledge Graph, Data Platforms, Digital Twins, University Platforms, Managed Services. Design must be elegant, expensive, responsive, and not a generic card dump. Use subtle hover and reveal animations. No fake claims. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 57 |   },\\\\n 58 |   {\\\\n 59 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"07-homepage-interactive-experience\\\\\\\",\\\\n 60 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Complete Interactive Experience section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 61 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 62 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Interactive Experience tools section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 63 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 64 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Verify or restore the Interactive Experience section on the homepage. It must include Talk to Agent, Blueprint Generator, AI Readiness, ROI Calculator, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio. Link to /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /platforms/marketplace or /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio or /platforms/foundry. If an existing BuildAIEnterpriseSection or similar approved section exists, update it minimally instead of replacing it. The design should feel like premium self-service enterprise tools, with tasteful cards or tabs, subtle motion, frontend-only preview behavior, no real API calls, and no fake outputs. Avoid nested boxes and excessive badges. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 65 |   },\\\\n 66 |   {\\\\n 67 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"08-homepage-global-presence\\\\\\\",\\\\n 68 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add Global Presence section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 69 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 70 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Global Presence\\\\\\\",\\\\n 71 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 72 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add or restore the Global Presence section on the homepage. Include Singapore as Global Headquarters, London UK as Client Innovation Centre or Client Center, India as AI Engineering Factory or Build Shop, and future regions Australia, Middle East, USA. Use an existing world map component if available. If not, create a lightweight SVG/CSS global hub visual or premium region grid. Do not add a heavy 3D globe dependency. Do not invent office addresses. Do not invent fake headcount unless already approved in content. Make the UI clean, cinematic, enterprise-grade, responsive, and aligned with landing theme. Add subtle motion or hover states. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 73 |   },\\\\n 74 |   {\\\\n 75 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"09-homepage-client-success\\\\\\\",\\\\n 76 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add Client Success section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 77 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 78 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Client Success\\\\\\\",\\\\n 79 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 80 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add or restore the homepage Client Success section. Required elements: Case Studies, Video, Architecture, Business Outcomes. Use only anonymized representative patterns, never fake clients or fake logos. Representative patterns may include Global Banking Transformation, Healthcare Knowledge Operations, Manufacturing AI Factory, Retail Agent Operations. Label them as representative patterns. No fake numbers, no fake ROI, no fake customer names. Create a premium design with tabs, carousel, or narrative cards if appropriate. Include an architecture preview panel and outcome themes such as faster decision making, reduced manual effort, better knowledge access, improved compliance workflows, and improved employee experience. Mobile friendly. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 81 |   },\\\\n 82 |   {\\\\n 83 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"10-homepage-live-dashboard\\\\\\\",\\\\n 84 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add Live Dashboard preview section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 85 |     \\\\\\\"scope\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"homepage-section\\\\\\\",\\\\n 86 |     \\\\\\\"target\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Live Dashboard\\\\\\\",\\\\n 87 |     \\\\\\\"allowLandingChanges\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n 88 |     \\\\\\\"prompt\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Add or restore the homepage Live Dashboard section. Required labels: Active Clients, Agents Running, AI Projects, Countries, Industries, Agent Health, Delivery, Spend, Adoption, Governance. Do not invent precise values. You may use only approved values such as 500+ AI Use Cases and 20+ Industries where appropriate. Other dashboard items must be label-only states such as Monitoring-ready, Connected in Control Center, Frontend preview, or Governance-ready. Design should feel like a premium enterprise AI operations control center, not a crypto dashboard. Use subtle animated status lines, charts without fake data, and clean dashboard panels. No backend, no real-time claims. Responsive and accessible. Run lint/build.\\\\\\\"\\\\n 89 |   },\\\\n 90 |   {\\\\n 91 |     \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"11-homepage-latest-research\\\\\\\",\\\\n 92 |     \\\\\\\"title\\\\\n[... output truncated: 1213318 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nully integrated:\\\\n    1. **Hero**: `HeroSection` (Present)\\\\n    2. **Enterprise Quick Search**: `QuickSearchSection` (Present)\\\\n    3. **Garage Foundry Factory journey**: `JourneySection` (Present)\\\\n    4. **What We Build**: `WhatWeBuildSection` (Present)\\\\n    5. **Interactive Experience**: `InteractiveExperienceSection` (Present)\\\\n    6. **Global Presence**: `GlobalPresenceSection` (Present)\\\\n    7. **Client Success**: `ClientSuccessSection` (Present)\\\\n    8. **Live Dashboard**: `LiveDashboardSection` (Present)\\\\n    9. **Latest Research**: `LatestResearchSection` (Present)\\\\n    10. **Contact**: `ContactSection` (Present)\\\\n    11. **Footer**: `Footer` (Present)\\\\n  - **Other Active Sections**: `TalkToAgentSection`, `BuildAIEnterpriseSection`, `FoundrySection`, `IndustrySolutionsSection`, `InsightsSection`, `GarageSection`.\\\\n  - **Anomalies / Observations**: `ProductizedAssetsSection` is imported on line 13 of `components/LandingPage.tsx` but is never rendered inside the JSX.\\\\n\\\\n#### 6. Blueprint Scoring Formula & Banking Test Case\\\\n* **Status: GAP IDENTIFIED**\\\\n* **Findings**:\\\\n  - The scoring formula in `lib/blueprint-data.ts` works mathematically based on the weights:\\\\n    $$\\\\\\\\text{Score} = (AI\\\\\\\\_Maturity \\\\\\\\times 0.20) + (Business\\\\\\\\_Need \\\\\\\\times 0.25) + (Data\\\\\\\\_Readiness \\\\\\\\times 0.20) + (Process\\\\\\\\_Complexity \\\\\\\\times 0.20) + (Transformation\\\\\\\\_Readiness \\\\\\\\times 0.15)$$\\\\n  - However, in `components/sections/BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx` (lines 135-141), the scores passed to the formula are currently hardcoded for simulation:\\\\n    ```typescript\\\\n    const score = calculateBlueprintScore({\\\\n      aiMaturityScore: 60,\\\\n      businessNeedScore: 80,\\\\n      dataReadinessScore: 50,\\\\n      processComplexityScore: 50,\\\\n      transformationReadinessScore: 80\\\\n    });\\\\n    ```\\\\n    This results in a static score of **64** for any answers provided by the user.\\\\n  - The required Banking test case (**Banking, 15000 employees, Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved**) does not map to dynamic inputs and thus does not return **87/100**.\\\\n  - **Resolution Need**: In future tasks, we need to map user selections to dynamic maturity values and ensure the specified banking test case evaluates exactly to **87**.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n### Design System Observations\\\\n* Refined, premium visual styling (dark `#010101` and `#000613` backgrounds, glassmorphism card design, glowing color maps).\\\\n* Seamless custom SVG iconography, premium gradients (`#E4000F` to `#009DFF`), and balanced responsive layouts.\\\\n* Clean visual hierarchy adhering strictly to the Apple-like \\\\\\\"Apple 2026 Enterprise AI\\\\\\\" standard, without excessive badging or generic robot imagery.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n### Validation Baseline\\\\n* **Linting**: Passed successfully.\\\\n* **Static compilation (`npm run build`)**: Compiled successfully in `6.0s` with zero errors.\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n### Recommended Next Task\\\\n* **Task ID**: `01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage` to ensure that any potential routing folders or leftover catch-all directories are completely cleared from the project and that the base explicit App Router folders are clean before adding explicit files. Or proceed immediately to scoring logic alignment under task `10-verify-and-fix-blueprint-generator-scoring`.\\\"}}\\n./automation/logs/2026-06-25T22-42-26-390Z-00-preflight-project-context-implement.log:209:{\\\"ts\\\":\\\"2026-06-25T22:42:25.930Z\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent_event\\\",\\\"event\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"content_end\\\",\\\"contentType\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"**Confirming Project Stability**\\\\n\\\\nI'm incredibly pleased to report that both `npm run lint` and `npm run build` completed successfully, producing zero errors. This indicates a stable codebase and a straightforward build process, which is a significant win.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Analyzing Current Infrastructure**\\\\n\\\\nI've just concluded the technical audit. I've discovered the project uses Next.js (v16.2.9) with React (v19.2.4) and employs the Next.js App Router. Styling is handled by Tailwind CSS (v4) with utility classes and custom CSS. Animation is achieved through `motion/react` (v12.40.0). Notably, I've identified significant gaps in the routing model, with several key public pages missing.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Evaluating Routing Compliance**\\\\n\\\\nI've been meticulously examining the missing app router files. I can confirm the absence of specific routes, such as `/industries/banking` and `/platforms/blueprint`. I also found that critical `app/[...slug]/page.tsx` and `components/PublicRoutePage.tsx` are missing. These gaps do perfectly align with the prescribed non-negotiable routing constraints, which is a key observation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Assessing Page Section Hierarchy**\\\\n\\\\nI've been examining the section rendering within the landing page. Key sections like `GlobalPresenceSection`, `ClientSuccessSection`, and `ContactSection` are present, but also found extra non-standard sections such as `TalkToAgentSection` and `IndustrySolutionsSection`, which are rendered. I also observed `ProductizedAssetsSection` is imported but not rendered. Furthermore, only two Aceternity UI components exist in the codebase: `world-map.tsx` and `3d_view.tsx`.\\\\n\\\\nI've examined the `lib/blueprint-data.ts` file, and confirmed the formula for scoring, as well as test case (banking).\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Addressing Blueprint Scoring**\\\\n\\\\nI've pinpointed a major flaw in the AI Enterprise section. The `calculateBlueprintScore` function is receiving hardcoded values, resulting in a static score of 64. My \\\\\\\"Banking\\\\\\\" test case demands an 87/100, which confirms the gap. The generator needs to dynamically map user inputs to maturity scores. I now see my next task is to verify and fix the blueprint generator scoring mechanism, or to perform a final safety cleanup step.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\"}}\\n./automation/tasks.json:8:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a preflight audit only. Do not edit files. Inspect package.json, app route tree, app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/sections, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/landing-data.ts, lib/blueprint-data.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, and components/CommandCenter.tsx if they exist. Confirm the framework, routing model, styling stack, animation libraries, current page architecture, and whether framer-motion or motion/react is installed. Confirm whether any Aceternity UI components already exist; do not install anything. Check that there is no app/[...slug]/page.tsx and no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx. Search for PublicRoutePage imports and slug catch-all references. Check whether the landing page has all required homepage sections: Hero, Enterprise Quick Search, Garage Foundry Factory journey, What We Build, Interactive Experience, Global Presence, Client Success, Live Dashboard, Latest Research, Contact, Footer. Check whether all public pages are explicit App Router pages. Check whether the Blueprint scoring formula exists and whether the banking test case can return 87/100. Produce a gap list only. Do not edit files. Final response must include files inspected, missing items, route gaps, homepage gaps, design-system observations, animation-library availability, and recommended next task.\\\"\\n./automation/tasks.json:11:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage\\\",\\n./automation/tasks.json:12:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Remove forbidden slug route leftovers\\\",\\n./automation/tasks.json:16:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Implement only routing safety cleanup. Remove any forbidden catch-all slug route leftovers. There must be no app/[...slug]/page.tsx, no empty app/[...slug] directory, no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx, and no imports or references to PublicRoutePage. Do not redesign anything. Do not touch the landing page. Ensure all public pages remain explicit App Router pages. If an explicit page is missing, create a minimal explicit page file that uses the existing shared inner-page template, not slug logic. Run lint and build. Acceptance: no module-not-found for PublicRoutePage, no slug route files, no slug references, build passes, landing page unchanged.\\\"\\n./automation/tasks.json:112:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Verify and complete the public navigation, footer, and sitemap route links. Do not redesign header or footer. Keep the current approved visual style. Header must include HOME, WHY GFF AI, CAPABILITIES, INDUSTRIES, PLATFORMS, BUILD WITH GFF, RESOURCES, COMPANY, CONTACT, CLIENT LOGIN. Footer must include Quick Links, Solutions, Industries, Platforms, Company, Legal, Newsletter where current layout supports it. Required legal/support links: Privacy, NDA, Terms, Investor Relations, Client Portal. All hrefs must resolve to explicit pages. Do not use slug routing. Do not create fake newsletter sending; frontend-only state only. Run lint/build.\\\"\\n./automation/tasks.json:296:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Audit all nav, footer, homepage section, CTA, related-link, card, carousel, tab, and form links. Fix broken or incorrect links only. Ensure all public pages are explicit. Ensure no href points to removed slug/catch-all paths. Check that required public routes exist: top-level, Why GFF AI, Capabilities, Industries, Platforms, Build, Resources, Company, Contact, Portal, Client, Insights, Privacy, Terms, NDA, Investor Relations. Ensure content includes GFF AI positioning, Garage Foundry Factory, global footprint, research/IP where appropriate, and no fake data. Run lint/build.\\\"\\n./automation/tasks.json:304:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for the complete Phase 0 to Phase 2 build. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify landing page has approved hero preserved, hero video placement unchanged, hero copy and metrics correct, Enterprise Quick Search present and local, Garage Foundry Factory journey present, What We Build present, Interactive Experience present, Global Presence present, Client Success present, Live Dashboard present without fake numbers, Latest Research present, Footer complete. Verify explicit routes exist and no slug logic or PublicRoutePage exists. Verify all public pages have premium unique UI, category design families, mobile responsiveness, accessibility basics, no fake data, no backend/API/AWS/auth/OTP/export behavior. Verify Blueprint banking test returns 87/100. Run npm run lint and npm run build if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed in final QA, commands run, remaining warnings, and any remaining TODOs.\\\"\\n\",\"success\":true}],\"durationMs\":1146}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-25T22-48-10-289Z-01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage-implement.log:26:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-25T22:47:42.739Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Verifying File Structure**\\n\\nI'm now diving deeper into the file structure within the `app/` directory. My focus is on verifying any potential alternative locations or related files for the slug variable. I need to make sure I am covering all grounds. I'm re-examining the directory tree to eliminate any missed paths.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-25T22-48-10-289Z-01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage-implement.log:30:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-25T22:47:43